Source: BelTA News Agency, Belarus, 20 Jun 2001 [edited

Crimean-Congo Hemorrhagic Fever in Russia: 25 Cases, 3 Deaths
-------------------------------------------------------------
MOSCOW: As of Wed 20 Jun 2001, 25 cases of Crimean-Congo
hemorrhagic fever (CCHF) have been recorded in Russia, with 3
deaths. The Russian State Medical Service has reported that cases have
been registered in the Stavropol, Dagestan, Kalmykiya, Volgograd,
Astrachan and Rostov-on-Don areas. The source of infection is CCHF-
infected ticks. A total of 33 persons required hospital treatment
following tick bites: 12 in the Stavropol area, 14 in Dagestan, and 7
persons in the Volgograd area.
Since the beginning of the year a total of 4724 persons in Russia have
sought medical attention following tick bites, in situations where there
has been a suspicion of CCHF infection. The Stavropol region has
accounted for the majority (3238).
